From 3d7423e1944b55d5cbaa53ded1790e81c057555f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:49:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] diag: cap VESA mode enumeration at 16bpp via
 SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8 perf companion to patches/SDL/0006-vbe-max-bpp-hint. NXEngine
sets SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP="16" at OVERRIDE priority before SDL_Init so
SDL3-DOS's mode enumeration filters out 24bpp+ modes. Result on the
g2k Mach64: VESA mode 0x111 (640×480×16bpp pitch=1280) is chosen
instead of 0x112 (640×480×24bpp pitch=2560), dropping per-frame
framebuffer flush from 921 KB to 614 KB.

We don't go to 8bpp yet — a quick test produced "Texture doesn't have
a palette" errors flooding DEBUG.LOG because NXEngine's renderer
pipeline isn't palette-ready end-to-end (Phase 9 lever 3 work). 16bpp
sidesteps that.

Trade-off: under DOSBox-X parity 16bpp is ~8× slower per flip than
24bpp because the SDL3 software-renderer's 24->16bpp conversion is
slow under emulation. On real Mach64 the conversion is CPU-bound
(~10 ms amortized) while the flush is bandwidth-bound (~2.8 s
measured at 24bpp), so 16bpp should net faster on real HW. Verify on
g2k.
---
 src/main.cpp | 31 +++++++++++++++++++++----------
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 470847d..0b7b828 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -357,17 +357,28 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   // in the normal path's banked-mode blit (line 806+). Forcing the fast
   // path bypasses that whole branch.
   //
-  // Our use case doesn't need what the normal path adds:
-  //   - cursor compositing — game runs fullscreen, no SDL software cursor;
-  //   - palette sync between window and src surfaces — we use a single
-  //     surface format end to end;
-  //   - vsync — Pentium-class hardware can't sustain >50 FPS reliably anyway;
-  //   - page flipping — banked mode (which DOSBox-X's emulated 320x240 hits)
-  //     doesn't use page flipping in the normal path either.
-  //
-  // So forcing the fast path is cheaper for us regardless of whether the
-  // normal-path bug ever gets fixed.
+  // 2026-04-26 update: attempted to remove this in a Phase-8 perf experiment
+  // (would have engaged LFB on Mach64 instead of banked mode, ~10-15× speedup).
+  // Removal reproduced the original Phase 7 black-framebuffer wall under
+  // DOSBox-X (fb_state stays zero-initialized in the LFB code path —
+  // confirmed via patches/SDL/0002+0003 dump showing direct_fb=0 fb_size=0
+  // bpp=0 pixels=NULL). The hint stays for now; the proper fix lives in
+  // SDL_dosframebuffer.c's fb_state init for the LFB path and will land as
+  // a separate patch (tracked in docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md).
   SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER, "1", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+
+  // Patch 0041 (Phase 8 perf, 2026-04-26): cap SDL3-DOS VESA mode
+  // enumeration at 16bpp. Without this, SDL3's closest-mode matching picks
+  // 24bpp (mode 0x112 on the g2k Mach64; 32bpp 0x190 on DOSBox-X). 16-cap
+  // forces 0x111 (640×480×16) on Mach64 — drops per-frame framebuffer flush
+  // from 921 KB to 614 KB (~1.5× speedup).
+  //
+  // We don't go to 8bpp (which would be ~3× speedup) because NXEngine's
+  // renderer pipeline isn't palette-ready end-to-end yet — a quick test
+  // produced "Texture doesn't have a palette" errors flooding DEBUG.LOG.
+  // 8bpp end-to-end is Phase 9 lever 3 work; needs palette management on
+  // stage transitions. Tracked in docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md.
+  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP, "16", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
 #endif
 
   // SDL3: SDL_Init returns bool (true on success); old `< 0` check would always be false.
-- 
